
[1]laud

   LAUD, n. [L. laus, laudis; Gr. ; Eng. loud. See Loud.]

   1. Praise; commendation; an extolling in words; honorable mention.
   [Little used.]

   2. That part of divine worship which consists in praise.

   3. Music or singing in honor of any one.

     LAUD, v.t. [L. laudo.] To praise in words alone, or with words and
                           singing; to celebrate.
